Visualizing Dallas Dance's trips in 2016

Former Baltimore County school superintendent Dallas Dance traveled extensively during his time on the job, according to travel records obtained by The Baltimore Sun.

Many of these trips were to attend or speak at education-focused conferences and symposiums. 2016 was a particularly busy year for travel: records show that Dance spent over 80 days on the road for official school business during 2016 alone.

Here we visualize the out-of-town trips that Dance took in 2016; highlighting dates, destination, and costs to the taxpayer. Darker colors indicate overlapping events.
